That part which until 1.4.1935 formed parts of the parishes of 
    Burnham and Taplow. See also Table 2, note (d).

Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Eton and 
    Dorney.

That part which until 1.4.1935 formed part of the parish of 
    Gerrards Cross. See also Table 2, note (d).

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Eton. Abolished 
    1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Eton.

Created 1.10.1895 out of the parishes of Chalfont St. Peter, Fulmer, 
    Iver, Langley Marish and Upton cum Chalvey. See also Table 2, notes (a), 
    (c), 
    (d), (e) and (f).

Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Hedgereley, 
    Farnham Royal and Gerrards Cross.

Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Burnham, 
    Taplow and Dorney.

Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Wexham, 
    Fulmer and Iver.

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Upton cum Chalvey 
    in Stoke Urban District. Abolished 1.4.1974 to become an unparished area. See also Table 2, note 
    (g).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Stoke Poges in Slough 
    Urban District. Abolished 26.3.1896 and added to the parish of Slough.
Abolished 1.10.1901 and added to the parish of Wexham.
